The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques for stereo matching, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for learning similarity measures is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses post-processing steps that involve optimization and filtering, which could be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
